users. compress image without losing quality is a balance: you remove bytes humans barely see on small screens."}],["$","p","1",{"style":{"marginBottom":"1rem"},"children":"Start from the largest source file, resize to the display width you need, then compress. Doing only compression on a 6000px-wide photo wastes effort."}]]]}],["$","section","1",{"style":{"marginBottom":"2rem"},"children":[["$","h2",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1.15rem","marginBottom":"0.75rem"},"children":"JPEG, PNG, or WebP?"}],[["$","p","0",{"style":{"marginBottom":"1rem"},"children":"Photos: JPEG or WebP. Graphics with transparency: PNG or WebP. Modern browsers support WebP well—use jpg to webp converters when you control hosting."}],["$","p","1",{"style":{"marginBottom":"1rem"},"children":"For hero images, try 75–85 quality JPEG as a baseline, then compare visually at 100% zoom."}]]]}],["$","section","2",{"style":{"marginBottom":"2rem"},"children":[["$","h2",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1.15rem","marginBottom":"0.75rem"},"children":"Step-by-step workflow"}],[["$","p","0",{"style":{"marginBottom":"1rem"},"children":"Export from your editor at 2× max width of your layout column. Open an image compressor fast online tool, apply moderate compression, download, and upload. Clear CDN or cache after replacing files."}],["$","p","1",{"style":{"marginBottom":"1rem"},"children":"Use our image compressor to process locally when you do not want uploads to third-party APIs."}]]]}],["$","section","3",{"style":{"marginBottom":"2rem"},"children":[["$","h2",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1.15rem","marginBottom":"0.75rem"},"children":"Quick wins"}],[["$","p","0",{"style":{"marginBottom":"1rem"},"children":"Lazy-load below-the-fold images in your CMS. Add width and height attributes to reduce layout shift. Combine compression with CDN caching for repeat visitors."}]]]}]]}],["$","aside",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"2.5rem","padding":"1.25rem 1.5rem","borderRadius":"var(--radius)","border":"1px solid var(--border)","backgr